## 2. Data model

### Reused (already in 0001, applied)
- `knowledge` — the node (id, user_id, concept, description, embedding).
- `knowledge_links` — concept to source evidence (polymorphic `node_ref`).
- `resource` (read/watched), `artifact` (built), `experience` (did), `education`, `sources` —
  the source nodes. `resource` already has `summary`, `url`, `author`, `consumed_at`, `embedding`.
- `match_knowledge` RPC — ANN neighbors.

### Deltas (fold into 0001, idempotent, staged NOT applied)
```sql
create table if not exists knowledge_alias (
  knowledge_id uuid not null references knowledge(id) on delete cascade,
  alias        text not null,
  primary key (knowledge_id, alias));

create table if not exists knowledge_cluster (
  id         uuid primary key default gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id    uuid not null references person(id) on delete cascade,
  parent_id  uuid references knowledge_cluster(id) on delete cascade,
  label      text,
  centroid   halfvec(768),
  created_at timestamptz not null default now());

alter table knowledge add column if not exists cluster_id
  uuid references knowledge_cluster(id) on delete set null;
```
RLS owner-scoped on both new tables (copy existing pattern). No owned/strength/mode columns
(derived). `match_knowledge` to also return `description` (judge needs it) at wiring time.

