## 3. Pipeline

### Producers (extraction is producer-owned; ingest is shared)
- onboarding / resume (v1): resume parser already extracts skills. Map them to mentions with
  provenance and feed the funnel:
  - `XExperience.skills` -> ingest(ref_type=experience, ref_id) -> owned
  - `XArtifact.skills`   -> ingest(ref_type=artifact, ref_id)   -> owned
  - top-level `skills`   -> ingest(ref_type=source=resume)      -> encountered (mention)
- long content / share (next): chunk -> per-chunk extractor returns (concepts + chunk summary)
  -> aggregator returns (deduped concepts + one doc-level summary). Same extract prompt as
  resume + one aggregator prompt. Store the doc summary on `resource.summary` + embed it
  (searchable source, powers branding/connection). Chunk summaries are intermediate, discarded.
  No chunk table (provenance is source-level).
- learning module, report (later): create artifact/experience/education -> ingest -> owned/practicing.

### Ingest funnel (shared chokepoint, `knowledge_ingest.ingest`)
```
normalize (LLM)          raw mention -> canonical concept + glossary description
dedup
  exact name / alias     store.find_exact -> reuse
  ANN recall             store.neighbors (match_knowledge), replaces numpy fullscan
  3-zone                 sim >= MERGE -> auto-merge | [NEW,MERGE) -> LLM judge | < NEW -> new
  on merge               fold description (LLM, if adds info) + re-embed + write alias
link                     store.link(concept, source) -> evidence edge
```

### Derive (on read, no recompute)
- `owned(user, concept)` and `strength(user, concept)` are pure functions over the concept's
  evidence links + the linked source kinds. Computed when a consumer asks. Materialize later
  only if hot reads demand it.

### Cluster (emergent, per-user, batch)
- build kNN graph from `match_knowledge` over the user's concepts -> hierarchical community
  detection (Leiden / recursive) -> LLM labels each cluster. Multi-level via `parent_id`.
  No fixed L0 canopy in v1 (a stable canopy is deferred). Runs as a batch, not per-ingest.

