## 4. Build steps

All steps run against `InMemoryKnowledgeStore` (offline) until S6. Each ships with tests.

- S0  derive: `owned` + `strength` pure functions + unit tests. No schema.
- S1  store seam: `KnowledgeStore` protocol + Supabase/InMemory impls. DONE.
- S2  ingest hardening: ANN via `store.neighbors`, `find_exact` + alias fast-path, description
      fold + re-embed. Migrate existing ingest tests to the in-mem store.
- S2p onboarding producer: resume extraction skills -> `Mention[]` with provenance -> ingest.
      First end-to-end path (resume-first v1).
- S3  clustering: emergent hierarchical clusters + LLM labels (per-user) on fixtures.
- S4  long-doc producer: chunk -> extract (concepts + chunk summary) -> aggregator (concepts +
      doc summary). Store doc summary on resource. Own eval.
- S5  eval harness over the corpus: extraction precision/recall, dedup, homonym false-merge.
      Author gold labels in `data/knowledge_corpus/gold/`.
- S6  Supabase store impl + fold DDL into 0001 (alias, cluster, cluster_id). Staged, NOT applied.
- S7  wire producers to real endpoints + apply migration on a branch + e2e. Add per-user
      advisory lock for concurrent ingest.

---

## 5. Test plan

- Unit (mocked LLM/embed, in-mem store): normalize, 3-zone dedup, alias fast-path, desc fold,
  owned/strength derivation, mode-from-source mapping, cluster assignment.
- Validation-before-build (scripts/): homonym false-merge rate (gates the auto-merge band),
  strength ordering monotonic, cluster label quality.
- Eval harness (scripts/, vs corpus): per-tunnel extraction precision/recall against gold;
  threshold calibration.
- E2E (real Supabase, branch): each tunnel full path; concurrent-ingest no-dup; "read N months
  ago" query; cluster assignment.
- CI: `pytest` green before each step merges.

Corpus: `data/knowledge_corpus/` (16 curated items across resume / paper / brief / video,
each with a stated purpose in the manifest). Builder: `scripts/build_knowledge_corpus.py`.

---

## 6. Deferred (parked, not v1)
- Wikidata QID / type enrichment — a separate, isolated step gated by its own precision pass
  (top-5 + P31 type-filter + LLM-confirm; naive top-1 measured at ~64% precision). Build when
  cross-module (job / network) matching needs a shared join key. Off the description path
  (description is LLM-generated).
- `concept_edge` typed concept-to-concept relations (real-graph features).
- Global / per-agency concept catalog (per-user now; `knowledge.user_id` is the claim).
- Stable L0 cluster canopy (emergent-only for v1).
- Auto-merge threshold policy — revisit after the homonym eval.

## 7. Open at build time (not design gaps)
- Gold labels for the corpus.
- Threshold calibration (NEW/MERGE, cluster params, strength constants) on real data.
